TEXT.TITLE: DUTCH ADJUSTED UNEMPLOYMENT UNCHANGED IN FEBRUARY
TEXT.BODY: Dutch seasonally-adjusted unemployment totalled 690,600 people in February, unchanged from January but down from 732,700 in February 1986, a Social Affairs Ministry spokesman said. The unadjusted figure stood at 708,700 at the end of last month, a decline of 3,800 from the January total of 712,500 and comparing with 750,000 at the end of February last year. REUTER
